<?xml version="1.0"?>
<h:html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms" xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:ev="http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:jr="http://openrosa.org/javarosa" xmlns:orx="http://openrosa.org/xforms" xmlns:odk="http://www.opendatakit.org/xforms" xmlns:cht="https://communityhealthtoolkit.org">
  <h:head>
    <h:title>Inputs Contact</h:title>
    <model odk:xforms-version="1.0.0">
      <itext>
        <translation lang="English (en)">
          <text id="/data/intro:label">
            <value>As noted in [the documentation](https://docs.communityhealthtoolkit.org/apps/guides/forms/form-inputs/#inputs-data-for-contact-in-app-forms), when opening an app form from a contact's profile page, data for that contact will be available in the &lt;code&gt;inputs/contact&lt;/code&gt; group.

However, when opening the same form from the "Reports" tab, this group will not be populated by default. A common pattern to handle this is to display/hide the actual &lt;code&gt;inputs&lt;/code&gt; group based on the value of &lt;code&gt;inputs/source&lt;/code&gt;. The source will be "contact" if the form was opened from a profile page. If it is opened from the "Reports" tab, the source will be set to its default value.

Setting the top level &lt;code&gt;patient\_uuid&lt;/code&gt; (or &lt;code&gt;place\_uuid&lt;/code&gt;) field to the &lt;code&gt;inputs/contact/_id&lt;/code&gt; value will associate the report with the selected patient.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/data/inputs/contact/_id:label">
            <value>Select a contact</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/data/hello:label">
            <value> Hello: <output value=" /data/contact_name "/></value>
          </text>
        </translation>
      </itext>
      <instance>
        <data id="inputs_contact" version="20260114092102" prefix="J1!inputs_contact!" delimiter="#">
          <intro/>
          <inputs>
            <meta>
              <location>
                <lat/>
                <long/>
                <error/>
                <message/>
              </location>
            </meta>
            <source>user</source>
            <contact>
              <_id/>
              <name/>
            </contact>
          </inputs>
          <patient_uuid/>
          <contact_name/>
          <hello/>
          <meta tag="hidden">
            <instanceID/>
          </meta>
        </data>
      </instance>
      <instance id="contact-summary"/>
      <instance id="user-contact-summary"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/intro" readonly="true()" type="string"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/inputs" relevant="./source = 'user'"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/inputs/source" type="string"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/inputs/contact/_id" type="string"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/inputs/contact/name" type="string"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/patient_uuid" type="string" calculate="../inputs/contact/_id"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/contact_name" type="string" calculate="../inputs/contact/name"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/hello" readonly="true()" type="string"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/meta/instanceID" type="string" readonly="true()" jr:preload="uid"/>
    </model>
  </h:head>
  <h:body class="pages">
    <input ref="/data/intro">
      <label ref="jr:itext('/data/intro:label')"/>
    </input>
    <group ref="/data/inputs">
      <group ref="/data/inputs/contact">
        <input ref="/data/inputs/contact/_id" appearance="select-contact">
          <label ref="jr:itext('/data/inputs/contact/_id:label')"/>
        </input>
      </group>
    </group>
    <input ref="/data/hello">
      <label ref="jr:itext('/data/hello:label')"/>
    </input>
  </h:body>
</h:html>